POST /api/removeContactFromAccount Remove Contact From Account

removeContactFromAccount Method

Overview

This method will be used for removing a contact from an account.

Business Rule

  • Fields (import details, company details, accounts, owners, management, contact) under request must be mandatory.
  • On the response, status after saving will be displayed.

POST /api/deleteAccount Delete account

deleteAccount Method

Overview

This method will be used for archiving a account.

Business Rule

  • Fields (import details) under request must be mandatory.
  • On the response, status after saving will be displayed.

Usage

  • This will be used on archiving an account.

Request

Import Details

Field Name Data Type Description Mandatory
AgencyID string Agency ID yes
WebBusinessID integer Landlord Web Business ID yes
ID integer Landlord Account ID yes
Action string Web Service Action yes
PropertyID integer Property ID yes
ActionType string Web Service Action Type yes
WebID integer Transaction ID yes
RemoveWebID integer Transaction ID to be removed yes
ManagementBusinessID integer Management Business ID no
ReceiptNumber string Receipt Number no
ReceiptAmount double Receipt Amount no
MeetingID integer Meeting ID no
CommonID integer Common ID no
DebtorRunID integer Debtor Run ID no
DebtorAmountDue double Debtor Amount Due no

POST /api/addInformation Add information

addInformation Method

Overview

This method will be used for adding a information.

Business Rule

  • Fields (import details, company details, accounts, management, properties, contact) under request must be mandatory.
  • On the response, status after saving will be displayed.

Usage

  • This will be used on adding an information.

POST /api/addCompanyLogo Add company logo

addCompanyLogo Method

Overview

This method will be used for saving a company logo and update company details if necessary.

Business Rule

  • Fields (import details, company details, attachments) under request must be mandatory.
  • On the response, status after saving will be displayed.

Usage

  • This will be used on saving details and creating login credentials for agency.

Sample Response

Success:

{ "status": "success" }

Error:

{ "status": "error", "message": "" }

Note:

On Error message: use standard HTTP error codes but with some additional information.

POST /api/deleteStatement Delete statement

deleteStatement Method

Overview

This method will be used for removing a statement.

Business Rule

  • Fields (import details) under request must be mandatory.
  • On the response, status after removing will be displayed.

Usage

  • This will be used on deleting monthly statement details.

Request

Import Details

Field Name Data Type Description Mandatory
AgencyID string Agency ID yes
WebBusinessID integer Landlord Web Business ID yes
AccountID integer Landlord Account ID yes
Action string Web Service Action yes
PropertyID integer Property ID yes
ActionType string Web Service Action Type yes
WebID integer Transaction ID yes
RemoveWebID integer Transaction ID to be removed yes
ManagementBusinessID integer Management Business ID no
ReceiptNumber string Receipt Number no
ReceiptAmount double Receipt Amount no
MeetingID integer Meeting ID no
CommonID integer Common ID no
DebtorRunID integer Debtor Run ID no
DebtorAmountDue double Debtor Amount Due no
ImageOrderNumber integer Image Order Number no
TaskID integer Task ID no

Response

Field Name Data Type Description
status string This is the status after ingestion.

Sample Request

Landlord

POST /api/addEoy Add EOY

addEoy Method

Overview

This method will be used for saving EOY Financial statement details and attachments.

Business Rule

  • Fields (import details, company details, attachments) under request must be mandatory.
  • On the response, status after saving will be displayed.

Usage

  • This will be used on saving EOY financial statement details and attachments.

Request

Import Details

Field Name Data Type Description Mandatory
AgencyID string Agency ID yes
WebBusinessID integer Landlord Web Business ID yes
AccountID integer Landlord Account ID yes
Action string Web Service Action yes
PropertyID integer Property ID yes
ActionType string Web Service Action Type yes
WebID integer Transaction ID yes
RemoveWebID integer Transaction ID to be removed yes
StatementDate date Statement Date yes
ManagementBusinessID integer Management Business ID no
ReceiptNumber string Receipt Number no
ReceiptAmount double Receipt Amount no
MeetingID integer Meeting ID no
CommonID integer Common ID no
DebtorRunID integer Debtor Run ID no
DebtorAmountDue double Debtor Amount Due no
ImageOrderNumber integer Image Order Number no
TaskID integer Task ID no

Company Details

Field Name Data Type Description Mandatory
ID string Agency ID yes
Name string Company Name no
ContactID integer Contact ID yes
Contact string Contact Name no
Address1 string Address 1 no
Address2 string Address 2 no
BusinessNumber string Business Number no
eMail string Email Address no
StreetNo string Street Number no
Street string Street Name no
Suburb string Suburb Name no
State string State Code no
Postcode string Postcode no
Country string Country no

Attachments

Field Name Data Type Description Mandatory
Filename string Filename yes
InlineAttachment string Inline Attachment yes

Response

Field Name Data Type Description
status string Status after ingestion

POST /api/deleteEoy Delete EOY

deleteEoy Method

Overview

This method will be used for removing EOY Financial statement details.

Business Rule

  • Fields (import details) under request must be mandatory.
  • On the response, status after removing will be displayed.

Usage

  • This will be used on removing EOY Financial statement details.

Request

Import Details

Field Name Data Type Description Mandatory
AgencyID string Agency ID yes
WebBusinessID integer Landlord Web Business ID yes
AccountID integer Landlord Account ID yes
Action string Web Service Action yes
PropertyID integer Property ID yes
ActionType string Web Service Action Type yes
WebID integer Transaction ID yes
RemoveWebID integer Transaction ID to be removed yes
ManagementBusinessID integer Management Business ID no
ReceiptNumber string Receipt Number no
ReceiptAmount double Receipt Amount no
MeetingID integer Meeting ID no
CommonID integer Common ID no
DebtorRunID integer Debtor Run ID no
DebtorAmountDue double Debtor Amount Due no
ImageOrderNumber integer Image Order Number no
TaskID integer Task ID no

Response

Field Name Data Type Description
status string This is the status after ingestion.

POST /api/addImages Add images

addImages Method

Overview

This method will be used for adding an image for a property.

Business Rule

  • Fields (import details, company details, accounts, owners, management, properties, contact, attachments) under request must be mandatory.
  • On the response, status after saving will be displayed.

Usage

  • This will be used on adding an image for a property.

Request

Import Details

Field Name Data Type Description Mandatory
AgencyID string Agency ID yes
WebBusinessID integer Landlord Web Business ID yes
ID integer Landlord Account ID yes
Action string Web Service Action yes
PropertyID integer Property ID yes
ActionType string Web Service Action Type yes
WebID integer Transaction ID yes
RemoveWebID integer Transaction ID to be removed no

Sample Response

Success:

{ "status": "success" }

Error:

{ "status": "error", "message": "" }

Note:

On Error message: use standard HTTP error codes but with some additional information.

POST /api/deleteImages Delete images

deleteImages Method

Overview

This method will be used for removing an image for a property.

Business Rule

  • Fields (import details) under request must be mandatory.
  • On the response, status after saving will be displayed.

Usage

  • This will be used on removing an image for a property.

Request

Import Details

Field Name Data Type Description Mandatory
AgencyID string Agency ID yes
WebBusinessID integer Landlord Web Business ID yes
ID integer Landlord Account ID yes
Action string Web Service Action yes
PropertyID integer Property ID yes
ActionType string Web Service Action Type yes
WebID integer Transaction ID yes
RemoveWebID integer Transaction ID to be removed yes
ManagementBusinessID integer Management Business ID no
ReceiptNumber string Receipt Number no
ReceiptAmount double Receipt Amount no
MeetingID integer Meeting ID no
CommonID integer Common ID no
DebtorRunID integer Debtor Run ID no
DebtorAmountDue double Debtor Amount Due no
ImageOrderNumber integer Image Order Number no
TaskID integer Task ID no

Note:

POST /api/addRpInspect Add RPInspect

addRpInspect Method

Overview

This method will be used for adding an inspection detail and attachment.

Business Rule

  • Fields (import details, company details, accounts, owners, management, properties, contact) under request must be mandatory.
  • On the response, status after saving will be displayed.

Usage

  • This will be used on adding an inspection detail and attachment.

Request

Import Details

Field Name Data Type Description Mandatory
AgencyID string Agency ID yes
WebBusinessID integer Landlord Web Business ID yes
ID integer Landlord Account ID yes
Action string Web Service Action yes
PropertyID integer Property ID yes

WebID integer Transaction ID yes

ReceiptAmount double Receipt Amount no

POST /api/deleteRpInspect Delete RPInspect

deleteRpInspect Method

Overview

This method will be used for removing an inspection detail and attachment.

Business Rule

  • Fields (import details) under request must be mandatory.
  • On the response, status after saving will be displayed.

Usage

  • This will be used on removing an inspection detail and attachment.

Request

Import Details

Field Name Data Type Description Mandatory
AgencyID string Agency ID yes
WebBusinessID integer Landlord Web Business ID yes
ID integer Landlord Account ID yes
Action string Web Service Action yes
PropertyID integer Property ID yes

POST /api/addDebtorNotice Add debtor notice

addDebtorNotice Method

Overview

This method will be used for adding an invoice detail and attachment.

Business Rule

  • Fields (import details, company details, accounts, owners, management, properties, contact, insurance, attachments) under request must be mandatory.
  • On the response, status after saving will be displayed.

Usage

  • This will be used on adding an invoice detail and attachment.

Success:

Error:

Note:

On Error message: use standard HTTP error codes but with some additional information.

POST /api/deleteDebtorNotice Delete debtor notice

deleteDebtorNotice Method

Overview

This method will be used for removing an invoice detail and attachment.

Business Rule

  • Fields (import details) under request must be mandatory.
  • On the response, status after saving will be displayed.

Usage

  • This will be used on removing an invoice detail and attachment.

Request

Import Details

Field Name Data Type Description Mandatory
AgencyID string Agency ID yes
WebBusinessID integer Landlord Web Business ID yes
ID integer Landlord Account ID yes
Action string Web Service Action yes
PropertyID integer Property ID yes
ActionType string Web Service Action Type yes
WebID integer Transaction ID yes
RemoveWebID integer Transaction ID to be removed yes
ManagementBusinessID integer Management Business ID no
ReceiptNumber string Receipt Number no
ReceiptAmount double Receipt Amount no
MeetingID integer Meeting ID no
CommonID integer Common ID no
DebtorRunID integer Debtor Run ID no
DebtorAmountDue double Debtor Amount Due no
ImageOrderNumber integer Image Order Number no
TaskID integer Task ID no

Response

Field Name Data Type Description
status string This is the status after ingestion.

Success:

{ "status": "success" }

Error:

Note:

On Error message: use standard HTTP error codes but with some additional information.

POST /api/addReceipt Add receipt

addReceipt Method

Overview

This method will be used for adding a receipt detail and attachment.

Business Rule

  • Fields (import details, attachments) under request must be mandatory.
  • On the response, status after saving will be displayed.

Usage

  • This will be used on adding a receipt detail and attachment.

Request

Import Details

Field Name Data Type Description Mandatory
AgencyID string Agency ID yes
WebBusinessID integer Landlord Web Business ID yes
Account ID integer Landlord Account ID yes
Action string Web Service Action yes
PropertyID integer Property ID no
ActionType string Web Service Action Type yes
WebID integer Transaction ID yes
RemoveWebID integer Transaction ID to be removed no
ManagementBusinessID integer Management Business ID yes
ReceiptNumber string Receipt Number yes
ReceiptAmount double Receipt Amount yes
ReceiptDebtorNoticeDate date Receipt Debtor Notice Date yes
MeetingID integer Meeting ID no
CommonID integer Common ID yes
DebtorRunID integer Debtor Run ID no
DebtorAmountDue double Debtor Amount Due no
ImageOrderNumber integer Image Order Number no

Attachments

Field Name Data Type Description Mandatory
Filename string Filename ID yes
InlineAttachment string InlineAttachment yes

Response

Field Name Data Type Description
status string Status

POST /api/deleteReceipt Delete receipt

deleteReceipt Method

Overview

This method will be used for deleting a receipt detail and attachment.

Business Rule

  • Fields (import details) under request must be mandatory.
  • On the response, status after saving will be displayed.

Usage

  • This will be used on deleting a receipt detail and attachment.

Request

Import Details

Field Name Data Type Description Mandatory
AgencyID string Agency ID yes
WebBusinessID integer Landlord Web Business ID yes
Account ID integer Landlord Account ID yes
Action string Web Service Action yes
PropertyID integer Property ID no
ActionType string Web Service Action Type yes
WebID integer Transaction ID yes
RemoveWebID integer Transaction ID to be removed no
ManagementBusinessID integer Management Business ID yes
ReceiptNumber string Receipt Number yes
ReceiptAmount double Receipt Amount yes
ReceiptDebtorNoticeDate date Receipt Debtor Notice Date yes
MeetingID integer Meeting ID no
CommonID integer Common ID yes
DebtorRunID integer Debtor Run ID no
DebtorAmountDue double Debtor Amount Due no
ImageOrderNumber integer Image Order Number no

Response

Field Name Data Type Description
status string Status

POST /api/addMeeting Add meeting

addMeeting Method

Overview

This method will be used for adding a meeting detail and attachment.

Business Rule

  • Fields (import details, company details, accounts, owners, management, properties, contact, insurance, attachments) under request must be mandatory.
  • On the response, status after saving will be displayed.

Usage

  • This will be used on adding a meeting detail and attachment.

Request

Import Details

Field Name Data Type Description Mandatory
AgencyID string Agency ID yes
WebBusinessID integer Landlord Web Business ID yes
ID integer Landlord Account ID yes
Action string Web Service Action yes
PropertyID integer Property ID yes
ActionType string Web Service Action Type yes
WebID integer Transaction ID yes
RemoveWebID integer Transaction ID to be removed no
ManagementBusinessID integer Management Business ID no
ReceiptNumber string Receipt Number no
ReceiptAmount double Receipt Amount no
MeetingID integer Meeting ID no
CommonID integer Common ID no
DebtorRunID integer Debtor Run ID no
DebtorAmountDue double Debtor Amount Due no
ImageOrderNumber integer Image Order Number no
TaskID integer Task ID no

Company Details

Field Name Data Type Description Mandatory
ID string Agency ID yes
Name string Company Name no
ContactID integer Contact ID yes
Contact string Contact Name no
Address1 string Address 1 no
Address2 string Address 2 no
BusinessNumber string Business Number no
eMail string Email Address no
StreetNo string Street Number no
Street string Street Name no
Suburb string Suburb Name no
State string State Code no
Postcode string Postcode no
Country string Country no

Accounts

Field Name Data Type Description Mandatory

POST /api/deleteMeeting Delete meeting

addMeeting Method

Overview

This method will be used for removing a meeting detail and attachment.

Business Rule

  • Fields (import details) under request must be mandatory.
  • On the response, status after saving will be displayed.

Usage

  • This will be used on removing a meeting detail and attachment.

Request

Import Details

Field Name Data Type Description Mandatory
AgencyID string Agency ID yes
WebBusinessID integer Landlord Web Business ID yes
ID integer Landlord Account ID yes
Action string Web Service Action yes
PropertyID integer Property ID yes
ActionType string Web Service Action Type yes
WebID integer Transaction ID yes
RemoveWebID integer Transaction ID to be removed yes
ManagementBusinessID integer Management Business ID no
ReceiptNumber string Receipt Number no
ReceiptAmount double Receipt Amount no
MeetingID integer Meeting ID no
CommonID integer Common ID no
DebtorRunID integer Debtor Run ID no
DebtorAmountDue double Debtor Amount Due no
ImageOrderNumber integer Image Order Number no
TaskID integer Task ID no

Response

Field Name Data Type Description
status string This is the status after ingestion.

POST /api/addContact Add contact

addContact Method

Overview

This method will be used for adding a contact on the contact list.

Business Rule

  • Fields (import details, company details, accounts, owners, management, properties, contact, insurance) under request must be mandatory.
  • On the response, status after saving will be displayed.

Usage

  • This will be used on adding a contact on the contact list.

POST /api/addOther Add other

addOther Method

Overview

This method will be used for adding a document.

Business Rule

  • Fields (import details, company details, accounts, owners, management, properties, contact, attachments) under request must be mandatory.
  • On the response, status after saving will be displayed.

Usage

  • This will be used on adding a document.

Success:

{ "status": "success" }

Error:

Note:

On Error message: use standard HTTP error codes but with some additional information.

POST /api/deleteOther Delete other

deleteOther Method

Overview

This method will be used for removing a document.

Business Rule

  • Fields (import details) under request must be mandatory.
  • On the response, status after saving will be displayed.

Usage

  • This will be used on removing a document.

Request

Import Details

Field Name Data Type Description Mandatory
AgencyID string Agency ID yes
WebBusinessID integer Landlord Web Business ID yes
ID integer Landlord Account ID yes
Action string Web Service Action yes
PropertyID integer Property ID yes
ActionType string Web Service Action Type yes
WebID integer Transaction ID yes
RemoveWebID integer Transaction ID to be removed yes
ManagementBusinessID integer Management Business ID no
ReceiptNumber string Receipt Number no
ReceiptAmount double Receipt Amount no
MeetingID integer Meeting ID no
CommonID integer Common ID no
DebtorRunID integer Debtor Run ID no
DebtorAmountDue double Debtor Amount Due no
ImageOrderNumber integer Image Order Number no
TaskID integer Task ID no

Success:

Error:

Note:

On Error message: use standard HTTP error codes but with some additional information.

Response status codes

Success

Successes differ from errors in that their body may not be a simple response object with a code and a message. The headers however are consistent across all calls:

  • GET, PUT, DELETE returns 200 OK on success,
  • POST returns 201 on success,

When retrieving stuff for example:

Status: 200 OK { { id: thing_1, name: 'My first thing' }, { id: thing_2, name: 'My second thing' } }

Error

Error responses are simply returning standard HTTP error codes along with some additional information:

  • The error code is sent back as a status header,
  • The body includes an object describing both the code and message (for debugging and/or display purposes),

For a call with an invalid HTTP authentication for example:

Status: 401 Unauthorized { code: 401, message: 'Unauthorized' }

Registration

How an integrator can be registered to the Portal

An integrator can be registered to the Portal by inserting a record on the database, until a user-interface has already been implemented to the Portal.

The web service username, password and integrator ID will be provided by the Super Admin. These credentials are needed to be able to successfully use the web service ingestion.

Postman setup

This will guide you on how to set-up your Postman to successfully send data via web-service. Note: Use Postman Google Chrome Extension

Step 1: Click Basic Auth. Enter the provided credentials (username, password) by the Super Admin. Then, click Refresh headers button.

Username: propmgr Password: propmgr999!

Step 2: On the Normal tab, add the following headers:

Accept: application/json Content-Type: application/json id: Integrator ID

Note: the Integrator ID will be provided by the Super Admin.

Step 3: Enter the path of the api on the URL.

An example would be:

http://stage.rppropertymanager.com.au/api/addCompany

Step 4: Choose POST for the method. On the request body, choose raw. Then, choose JSON on the drop-down.

Method: POST Request Body: raw Data Type: JSON

Authenticate

This method allows users to retrieve stuff.

Response

Sends back a collection of things.

Authentication: Basic { id: thing_2, name: 'My second thing' }

Note:

On Error message: use standard HTTP error codes but with some additional information.

Registration

When an integrator has been registered to the Portal, the following credentials will be provided:

  • Username
  • Password
  • Integrator ID

Using Postman

This will guide you on how to set-up your Postman to successfully send data via web-service. Note: Use Postman Google Chrome Extension

Step 1: Click Basic Auth. Enter the provided credentials (username, password) by the Super Admin. Then, click Refresh headers button.

Username: propmgr Password: propmgr999!

Step 2: Add the following headers:

Accept: application/json Content-Type: application/json id: Integrator ID

Note: the Integrator ID will be provided by the Super Admin.

Step 3: Enter the path of the api on the URL.

An example would be:

http://stage.rppropertymanager.com.au/api/addCompany

Step 4: Choose POST for the method. On the request body, choose raw. Then, choose JSON for the data format on the drop-down.

Method: POST Request Body: raw Data Type: JSON
